---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { getAppBySlug, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = getAppBySlug('gymmate')
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="Terms for using GymMate, including accounts, training data, Apple Health features, AI parsing, notifications, and availability."
>
  <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
  <p>
    By downloading, accessing, or using GymMate, you agree to these Terms of Use. If you do not
    agree, do not use the app. These Terms are in addition to, and do not replace, Apple&apos;s
    standard terms that apply to apps distributed through the App Store.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital Product
    Studio brand.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Description of the App</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate helps you plan training programs, log workouts, track progress, review statistics, manage
    warm-ups, use timers, export training data, receive optional reminders, and use Apple Watch or
    Apple Health features where available.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Accounts and Sign-In</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate uses account-backed features through Supabase. You may be able to sign in using email and
    password, Sign in with Apple, Google sign-in, or other supported methods shown in the app. You
    are responsible for keeping your device, account, and credentials secure.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use Sign in with Apple, your account access is subject to Apple&apos;s sign-in flow and
    your Apple ID settings. If you use Google sign-in, your account access is also subject to
    Google&apos;s sign-in flow and account settings.
  </p>

  <h2>4. User Responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for using GymMate lawfully, entering accurate information, keeping backups
    safe, and making sure you have the right to upload, store, share, or export any program text,
    notes, workout data, or other content you add to the app.
  </p>
  <p>
    You must not use GymMate to abuse the service, interfere with availability, bypass rate limits,
    misuse AI parsing, attempt unauthorized access, or upload content that violates applicable law or
    third-party rights.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Fitness, Health, and Safety</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate is provided for personal fitness organization and convenience. It is not medical advice,
    professional coaching, diagnosis, treatment, injury-prevention guidance, or a substitute for a
    qualified health, fitness, or medical professional.
  </p>
  <p>
    You are responsible for exercising safely, using proper technique, choosing suitable weights and
    exercises, stopping when needed, and consulting a qualified professional before starting or
    changing a training program if you have health concerns, injuries, or medical conditions.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Apple Health and Apple Watch</h2>
  <p>
    Apple Health, Apple Watch, Live Activity, widget, and notification features depend on device
    support, operating system permissions, Apple services, and your settings. Health and workout data
    shown by GymMate may be delayed, incomplete, or unavailable.
  </p>
  <p>
    You control Apple Health permissions through iOS and watchOS. GymMate is not responsible for
    Apple Health availability, Apple Watch connectivity, sensor accuracy, or decisions made based on
    device sensor data.
  </p>

  <h2>7. AI-Assisted Program Parsing</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate may offer AI-assisted parsing to convert workout text into structured programs. AI output
    can be incomplete, inaccurate, or unsuitable for your goals or health status. You are responsible
    for reviewing and editing any AI-generated or AI-parsed program before using it.
  </p>
  <p>
    AI parsing is subject to rate limits and may be changed, limited, suspended, or removed at any
    time to protect service reliability.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Your Content, Sync, and Exports</h2>
  <p>
    You keep ownership of the training content you add to GymMate, such as programs, exercises,
    workout logs, notes, body weight entries, warm-ups, and exports. You grant GymMate the limited
    permission needed to store, process, sync, display, analyze, and export that content so the app
    can provide its features.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate uses local storage and account-backed sync. Offline changes may remain on your device
    until connectivity returns. Exported files may contain personal training and health-related
    information, and you are responsible for where you save, share, or transmit those files.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Notifications</h2>
  <p>
    Reminders, weekly summaries, streak nudges, progress messages, push notifications, widgets, and
    Live Activities are optional convenience features. They may be delayed, unavailable, or affected
    by operating system settings, network availability, battery settings, or provider limitations.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    If GymMate offers paid plans, Pro features, in-app purchases, or subscriptions, the specific
    features, price, billing period, renewal terms, and any trial terms will be shown in the app
    before purchase. Apple-billed purchases, if offered, are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store.
  </p>
  <p>
    Subscription management, cancellations, and refund requests for Apple-billed purchases are
    handled through the user&apos;s Apple ID account and Apple&apos;s App Store settings. GymMate
    cannot directly cancel Apple-billed subscriptions or issue App Store refunds outside
    Apple&apos;s process.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Account Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate provides a way to request or initiate account deletion from within the app where
    available, subject to verification and legal retention requirements. Deleting the app may remove
    local app data from your device, but it may not automatically delete account-backed records,
    provider-side records, exported files, or copies you have saved elsewhere.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The app, its design, branding, code, templates, and related materials are protected by
    intellectual property laws. You may not copy, modify, distribute, or reverse engineer the app
    except where permitted by applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Availability and Changes</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate may be updated, changed, suspended, or discontinued at any time. Features may vary by
    platform, device, operating system version, App Store availability, network availability, account
    status, provider availability, or configuration.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, GymMate is provided as is and without warranties of any
    kind. We are not liable for indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising from
    use of the app, including injuries, training decisions, data loss, missed notifications, failed
    sync, unavailable exports, Apple Health issues, AI parsing errors, or reliance on app-generated
    recommendations and summaries.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about these Terms of Use, contact <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}
      >{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
